Lawrence Ernest PASTA, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 25983. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. July 2, 1968. Lawrence Ernest Pasta, pro se. Edward Boardman, U. S. Atty., John W. Caven, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., Jacksonville, Fla., for appellee.

Before WISDOM and COLEMAN, Circuit Judges, and MITCHELL, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

The judgment of the district court denying the motion of appellant to proceed under Section 2255, Title 28 is correct. Appellant’s relief is clearly precluded by the decision of this court in Rosecrans v. United States, 378 F.2d 561 (CA 5-1965) and by the decision of *953the Third Circuit in United States v. Gallagher, 183 F.2d 342 (CA 3-1950) cert. den. Gallagher v. United States, 340 U.S. 913, 71 S.Ct. 283, 95 L.Ed. 659.

Affirmed.
